<br>
You can always tell when someone's making a relic play because they start taking your forts. So if Albion's going for a relic, you play it smart and station a team at the Albion mile gate. If the Albs make off with the relic it's a safe bet that they'll burn their SoS to get away from the relic fort, so you just lie in wait at the mile gate and listen for your teammates at the relic keep to tell you what happened. If they burned away and no one could stop them, then the minstrels used SoS and won't have it when you gank them at their mile fort and take back your relic.<br>
<br>
Can't get any simpler. SoS does not make a minstrel god. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/10/02 11:25:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Minstrel RA SoS really is nasty</span><hr size=1> Ok let me tell you what I would do:<br>
<br>
1) Burn 2/3 SoS to get out of relic keep<br>
2) If anyone is chasing they will soon slow down as they try casting on you. The moment the Skald casts snare he is slowed for 10seconds, enought time for the group to dissapear.<br>
3) Take a different route home than the usual zone boundry, not too hard.<br>
4) when you are about to aproach the Albion MG let the ones that burned SoS run to the doors and open them, assuming doors need to be opened as most have been broken down already.<br>
5) the others follow and cast SoS when they meet a force at the MG.<br>
6) run to your PK, in total safety.<br>
7) gate over and the game is finished<br>
<br>
p.s. you may not even need to do step 1 as if there were still defenders around either the main relic force killed them or are in their persuit.<br>
<br>
